---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout title="Projects" description="Detailed information on every public AEGIS project — versions, licenses, status, and links.">
  <h1>Projects</h1>

  <section>
    <p>
      Each project in the AEGIS ecosystem has a defined scope, dedicated
      repository, and clear licensing terms. This page provides detailed
      information on every public-facing component.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS Constitution</h2>
    <p>
      The foundational governance charter for the AEGIS ecosystem. The
      Constitution defines eleven articles covering bounded capability, authority
      binding, deterministic enforcement, human oversight, information
      sovereignty, governance transparency, auditability, collective defense,
      deny-by-default operation, constitutional supremacy, and escalation
      discipline. It is the root of authority — every governance decision traces
      back to a constitutional article.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>Version</dt>
      <dd>v26.03.22</dd>
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>Apache 2.0</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>Published</dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://aegis-constitution.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aegis-constitution.com</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-constitution" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS Governance</h2>
    <p>
      The technical specification layer. AEGIS Governance hosts the AGP-1
      governance protocol, the ATX-1 threat matrix, the RFC process, and all
      formal specifications that translate constitutional principles into
      enforceable technical constraints. The ATX-1 taxonomy defines 10 tactics
      and 29 techniques for classifying threats to agentic AI systems.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>Key Artifact</dt>
      <dd>ATX-1 v2.1 (10 tactics, 29 techniques)</dd>
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>CC-BY-SA-4.0</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>Published</dd>
      <dt>DOI</dt>
      <dd><a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19251098" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">10.5281/zenodo.19251098</a></dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://aegis-governance.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aegis-governance.com</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-governance" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS Core</h2>
    <p>
      The canonical enforcement engine. aegis-core is a Python implementation
      of AGP-1 that evaluates governance policies at runtime. It provides
      deterministic policy evaluation, audit logging, and deny-by-default
      enforcement for AI systems. The runtime is well-tested and designed
      for production integration.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>Version</dt>
      <dd>v0.1.2</dd>
      <dt>Tests</dt>
      <dd>403 passing</dd>
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>BSL 1.1</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>Stable</dd>
      <dt>DOI</dt>
      <dd><a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19355478" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">10.5281/zenodo.19355478</a></dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-core" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS Platform</h2>
    <p>
      The operator-facing product layer. AEGIS Platform provides a dashboard
      for managing governance policies, an API surface for programmatic
      integration, and monitoring tools for runtime enforcement. It consumes
      aegis-core as its enforcement engine.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>Components</dt>
      <dd>Operator dashboard, API surface</dd>
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>Proprietary</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>In development</dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://aegis-platform.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aegis-platform.net</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS SDK</h2>
    <p>
      Client libraries for integrating AEGIS governance into applications.
      The SDK provides TypeScript and Python packages that handle authentication,
      policy evaluation requests, and audit log submission against the AEGIS
      Platform API.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>Languages</dt>
      <dd>TypeScript &amp; Python</dd>
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>BSL 1.1</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>Published</dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-sdk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS Docs</h2>
    <p>
      The public documentation site for the AEGIS ecosystem. Built with Astro,
      it provides developer guides, integration tutorials, the ATX-1 threat
      matrix browser, and technical reference for all AEGIS specifications
      and tools.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>Framework</dt>
      <dd>Astro</dd>
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>CC-BY-SA-4.0</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>Live</dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://aegis-docs.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aegis-docs.com</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-docs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS Federation</h2>
    <p>
      The cross-domain machine discovery protocol. AEGIS Federation defines how
      AEGIS-governed systems discover and verify each other across organizational
      boundaries. The protocol is specified in RFC-0016 and enables distributed
      governance without centralized coordination.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>Key Artifact</dt>
      <dd>RFC-0016</dd>
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>CC-BY-SA-4.0</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>Published</dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://aegis-federation.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aegis-federation.com</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-federation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="project">
    <h2>AEGIS Labs</h2>
    <p>
      The research sandbox. AEGIS Labs hosts experiments, adversarial testing
      scenarios, benchmark datasets, and exploratory work that informs the
      development of governance specifications and enforcement tools. Results
      from Labs feed into the formal RFC process.
    </p>
    <dl class="project-facts">
      <dt>License</dt>
      <dd>Apache 2.0</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd>Active</dd>
    </dl>
    <ul class="project-links">
      <li><a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-labs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocLayout>

<style>
  .project-facts {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 0.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .project-facts dt {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .project-facts dd {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .project-links {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .project-links a {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }
</style>
